
0) install packages
$ sudo apt-get install binutils libgdal1-1.5.0 postgresql-8.3 postgresql-8.3-postgis postgresql-server-dev-8.3 python-psycopg2 python-setuptools

0b) link gis scripts
$ sudo ln -s /usr/share/postgresql-8.3-postgis/{lwpostgis,spatial_ref_sys}.sql /usr/share/postgresql/8.3

1) setup postgres authentication
2) install geos
3) install proj4
4) install gdal
5) create spatial template
6) create postgis database

7) edit pg_hba.conf to allow db access
8) add /usr/local/lib to /etc/ld.so.conf and run ldconfig
